 in the areas to which people had to move. The contributors to this volume argue that there is a complexity, and a tension, inherent in trying to reconcile enforced displacement of people with the subsequent creation of a socio-economically viable and sustainable environment. Only when these are squarely confronted, will it be possible to adequately deal with the problems and to improve resettlement policies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aEconomic development projectszDeveloping countries. 0aForced migrationzDeveloping countries. 0aLand settlementzDeveloping countries. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh1 aBarutciski, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFisher, Eleanor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoenig, Dolores, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOliver-Smith, Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPandey, Balaji, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRew, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurton, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWet, Chris de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWet, Chris de, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781789203882?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781789203882423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781789203882/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK